    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="343"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 14, 1889</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 217.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    196, of May 27, 1889, concerning the vizerial letter to governors-general in
                    Turkey respecting American schools.</p>
                <p>I desire to offer the Department’s congratulations on the success which has so
                    far crowned your efforts in dealing with this troublesome and vexatious
                    question, and to express the hope that now many of the hardships which have
                    surrounded the American schools there, through arbitrary local interference, may
                    speedily disappear in the interest of a better and more satisfactory condition
                    of affairs.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
